# Dharohar MVP: Technical Architecture & Implementation

This document provides a detailed technical blueprint of the systems, workflows, and API endpoints implemented during this development cycle.

## 🏗️ System Architecture

The Dharohar platform is built as a high-performance **Full-Stack AWS Native Application**, moving away from local legacy databases toward a scalable, serverless-first infrastructure.

```mermaid
graph TD
    Client[React/Vite Frontend] -- HTTP/JWT --> API[Express.js Backend]
    
    subgraph "Identity & Access"
        API -- Admin SDK --> Cognito[AWS Cognito User Pool]
        Cognito -- User Data --> Dynamo[DynamoDB: UsersTable]
    end
    
    subgraph "Storage & Processing"
        API -- Presigned/Direct --> S3[S3 Media Bucket]
        API -- "Start Job" --> Transcribe[Amazon Transcribe]
        Transcribe -- Read/Write --> S3
        API -- "Invoke Model" --> Bedrock[AWS Bedrock: Claude 3]
        API -- "Persist Metadata" --> Dynamo[DynamoDB: AssetsTable]
    end
```

---

## 🔄 Core Workflows

### 1. Unified Authentication Flow
We replaced MongoDB with **AWS Cognito** as the source of truth for identity, while maintaining a mirrored profile in DynamoDB for fast metadata retrieval.

- **Step 1**: Frontend sends credentials to `/auth/login`.
- **Step 2**: Backend validates with Cognito and retrieves the User's Unique ID (Sub).
- **Step 3**: Backend fetches Role/Metadata from `UsersTable`.
- **Step 4**: Backend signs and returns a secure JWT containing the user's role.

### 2. AI Knowledge Extraction Pipeline (Sonic Assets)
This is the heart of the automated governance system, processing audio into structured cultural knowledge.

```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
    participant R as Reviewer (Frontend)
    participant B as Backend (Express)
    participant S3 as S3 Media
    participant T as Amazon Transcribe
    participant AI as Bedrock (Claude 3)
    participant DB as DynamoDB

    R->>B: PATCH /assets/:id/process
    B->>DB: Load Asset Metadata
    B->>T: StartTranscriptionJob (Media in S3)
    Note over B,T: Polling for Completion (ap-south-1)
    T-->>B: Job COMPLETED + JSON URI
    B->>S3: Download Transcript Text
    B->>AI: AnalyseAsset(Text + Metadata)
    Note over AI: Institutional Knowledge Extraction
    AI-->>B: Structured JSON Metadata
    B->>DB: Update Asset: aiProcessed = true
    B-->>R: 200 OK (Updated Asset)
```

---

## 📡 API Specifications

### Authentication
| Method | Endpoint | Description | Auth Required |
| :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- |
| `POST` | `/auth/login` | Authenticates via Cognito; returns JWT & Profile. | No |
| `POST` | `/auth/register` | Registers new user in Cognito & DynamoDB. | No |

### AI & Asset Management
| Method | Endpoint | Description | Role Required |
| :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- |
| `GET` | `/assets/pending` | Lists assets awaiting reviewer approval. | `review`, `admin` |
| `PATCH` | `/assets/:id/process` | **Triggers the AI Pipeline** (Transcribe + Bedrock). | `review`, `admin` |
| `GET` | `/assets/public` | Fetches assets for the landing page gallery. | Public |

*(Note: Authenticated routes require `Authorization: Bearer <token>`)*

---

## 💾 Data Modeling (DynamoDB)

We shifted to a **GSIs (Global Secondary Index)** pattern for performance:

1.  **`UsersTable`**: Partition Key: `userId`.
    - `email-index`: Used for fast lookup during various auth workflows.
2.  **`AssetsTable`**: Partition Key: `assetId`.
    - `creatorId-index`: Powers the "My Submissions" view.
    - `mediaFileId`: Links directly to the S3 object key.
    - `aiMetadata`: Stores the results of the Bedrock analysis.

---

## 🚀 Environment Configuration

The following critical variables were added to support the new services:

| Variable | Usage |
| :--- | :--- |
| `BEDROCK_REGION` | Usually `us-east-1` for model availability. |
| `BEDROCK_MODEL_ID` | `anthropic.claude-3-haiku-20240307-v1:0` |
| `MEDIA_BUCKET` | The target for audio and transcripts. |
| `COGNITO_USER_POOL_ID` | The ID of the dev authentication pool. |
